      { type:'short', q:"Identify and briefly explain the three withdrawals from the circular flow of income.", answer:"The three withdrawals are: (1) Savings — income not spent by households, removed from the flow; (2) Taxation — income taken by government reduces disposable income; (3) Imports — spending on foreign goods sends money out of the domestic economy." },
