      { type:'mc', q:"If the Marginal Propensity to Consume (MPC) is 0.8, the multiplier is:", options:["0.8","5","1.25","4"], answer:1, explanation:"Multiplier = 1 / (1 − MPC) = 1 / (1 − 0.8) = 1 / 0.2 = 5. An initial injection of spending is multiplied through the economy as each recipient spends a proportion of their income." },
